modules.description: This module handles low-level memory allocation aligned to page boundaries, providing functions to allocate, convert, and manipulate memory blocks. It works primarily with `Io_page.t` (page-aligned bigarrays) and `Cstruct.t` buffers, offering direct control over memory layout for tasks like device interfacing or custom memory management. Concrete use cases include allocating buffers for hardware communication, managing page-aligned memory pools, and converting between memory representations for efficient data transfer.
